  <p class="section-intro">Five historical precedents where technological revolutions created value for society while simultaneously destroying early shareholder capital.</p>
  <p class="body-text">The assumption that AI investment necessarily creates proportional economic value deserves serious scrutiny. History offers a consistent and sobering counterpoint — the largest capital expenditure cycles in technology have repeatedly generated both extraordinary winners and extraordinary capital destruction for early participants.</p>

