  <p class="section-intro">India's documented history of bypassing legacy technology generations — and why AI could follow the same pattern.</p>
  <p class="body-text">India's leapfrogging capability is not a theoretical construct. It is a documented, repeatable pattern across multiple technology domains spanning three decades. Each instance followed the same structure: the incumbent technology was expensive, entrenched, and dominant globally — and India bypassed it entirely to adopt the superior successor.</p>

