  <p class="body-text">India is not absent from AI. India possesses the <strong>world's second-largest AI talent base</strong>, an AI market growing at 39% CAGR, and 87% of surveyed companies already in active AI adoption stages. The IndiaAI mission provides national-scale policy support. The digital public infrastructure — Aadhaar, UPI, ONDC — provides a data and connectivity foundation that many AI applications require.</p>
  <p class="body-text">What India is avoiding is <strong>the speculative, capital-intensive frontier phase</strong> — the phase where GPT-5 training runs cost over $1 billion and data center investments require decades to generate returns. This is not absence. This is selection.</p>
